Rust Ecosystem Libraries
------------------------
This project uses various Rust crates from the ecosystem, each with their own
licenses. The exact licenses have been verified using `cargo license`:

Core Dependencies:
- tokio (MIT) - Asynchronous runtime
- serde (Apache-2.0 OR MIT) - Serialization framework
- clap (Apache-2.0 OR MIT) - Command line argument parsing
- anyhow (Apache-2.0 OR MIT) - Error handling
- reqwest (Apache-2.0 OR MIT) - HTTP client

Audio Processing Libraries:
- rubato (MIT) - Sample rate conversion
- rustfft (Apache-2.0 OR MIT) - Fast Fourier Transform
- hound (Apache-2.0) - WAV audio file handling

Security and System Libraries:
- ring (Apache-2.0 AND ISC) - Cryptographic operations
- dashmap (MIT) - Concurrent hash maps

For a complete list of all dependencies and their exact licenses, run:
`cargo license` in the project directory.

Full license texts and attribution information for all dependencies can be
found in their respective source repositories and documentation.

Python Libraries (References only)
----------------------------------
- RealtimeSTT (MIT) - Speech-to-text library

